This paper addresses the problem of text-to-text generation, specifically sentence-level paraphrasing, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The approach used in the paper involves machine learning techniques such as multiple-sequence alignment, which is a common technique in areas such as machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves working with unannotated corpora, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures (cs.DS).
